  @{fg shine}DoubleStart@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}DropObject@{fg text}
  S S
  The name of an object. Note that the attribute is only settable
  and that a previous call to AppMessage() must be done (or
  nothing will happen).

  @{fg shine}ForceQuit@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}HelpFile@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Iconified@{fg text}
  B SGN

  @{fg shine}MenuHelp@{fg text}
  N GN
  Notified when the user presses the help key on a menu item

  @{fg shine}MenuStrip@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Num1@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  An integral user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}Num2@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  An integral user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}Num3@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  An integral user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}OwnARexx@{fg text}
  B I
  It is so bad that we have an ARexx port opened and we can't get
  messages from it.If you specify OwnARexx you get the same port
  that would be opened (it means BASE if SingleTask=1 BASE.X if
  SingleTask=0) but internal in the macro. It means that you have
  to handle all the commands coming to the port, MUI ones too
  (e.g. QUIT)

  @{fg shine}SingleTask@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Sleep@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}String1@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  A string user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}String2@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  A string user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}String3@{fg text}
  S ISGN
  A string user attribute, usefull in situation like multiple
  macros project, or just as container for values

  @{fg shine}Title@{fg text}
  S I
  Should be supplied if UseCommodities=1

  @{fg shine}UseARexx@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}UseCommodities@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Version@{fg text}
  S IG

  @{fg shine}WantARexxCmd@{fg text}
  B I
  This attribute instructs the object to pass any ARexx command
  it receives to its port to the macro via AREXXCMD event.

